						<div class="postbody">The &quot;4 bits&quot; part was throwing me off. It sounds like you mean 4 units. A bit is like a digit in decimal; if something has 4 added to it, &quot;4 digits&quot; doesn't make sense.<br /><br />Explanations I have: I'm not grasping the sweep unit at the moment, the game is changing the channels manually and the sweep isn't doing anything, the sweep shift is not configured as you say, NSFPlay is showing the wrong channel values, NSFPlay has a bug in its sweep.<br />...<br />I ran a trace and I'm seeing 7F written to the sweep registers. I also see the game code writing these vibrato values to the channel's period, toggling it by 4. Have you tried breakpoints on other registers to see whether it's showing the right value? Or maybe it's resetting the sweep constantly so that it never actually fires.</div>

