			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you're using FCEUX, the display there &quot;helpfully&quot; indicates the value read from memory at that location (which is open bus), not the value you will write, the value in apu register, or anything else more useful.<br /><br />So when you set a breakpoint of &quot;$4001 != $FF&quot;, you get what blargg said. You'll want something more like &quot;break on writes of $4001 where A != $FF&quot; and then you get to hope that they used STA to write to the register instead of STX or STY.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
