			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The displayed APU pitch register values in NSFPlay 2.2 are actually incorrect (of by one, I think). If you want a more accurate display use the <a href="https://dl.dropbox.com/u/883356/nsfplay23b2.zip" class="postlink">NSFPlay 2.3 beta</a>. Also the correct behaviour of $4017 was not emulated at all until the 2.3 beta. The actually sweep function I think was correct in 2.2, if I recall, but the lack of $4017 control means Zelda II still had some timing errors and might sound incorrect as well. (TLDR: Get the 2.3 beta if you're not using it already.)<br /><br />At any rate, the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU" class="postlink">APU info on the wiki</a> should be correct at this point. If you find it doesn't explain how the sweep works with enough detail, I'd like some feedback on that so I can revise it to be clearer.</div>

